article.description: Josh Cuthbertson scored 12 points and Deion Holmes added 11 points to help South Carolina Upstate beat Navy 66-57 on Monday night.
article.headline: SC Upstate cruises against Navy, 66-57
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- Josh Cuthbertson scored 12 points and Deion Holmes added 11 points to help South Carolina Upstate beat Navy 66-57 on Monday night. Cuthbertson made all four of his field goal attempts, including 3 of 3 from 3-point range. Michael Buchanan and Jure Span both finished with nine points for the Spartans (3-9), who have won back-to-back games after losing nine of 10. The Spartans opened the second half on a 7-0 run and led 35-26 with 16:35 left. A Cuthbertson 3 pushed the lead past double figures and a second Cuthbertson triple extended it to a game-high 18 points (55-37) with 6:54 remaining. Navy (8-4) tried to battle back late, cutting the lead to 62-54 after two Jace Hogan free throws with 1:26 to go, but closest the Midshipmen got was seven. Hogan had 14 points and 12 boards to lead Navy.
